<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2728] JarRevision does not close URLConnections which are instances of HttpURLConnection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2728</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Android (unlike the regular JDK) does not clean up and close HttpURLConnection objects properly which can cause all manner of problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The initialize() method in JarRevision creates a URLConnection but never closes it because close() is only present in HttpURLConnection. We need a modified class which checks for the URLConnection being of type HttpURLConnection, and will correctly close() it at the end of the method.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Affects Felix running on Android</environment>
